{
  "stem": "19807.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were so well-- the-- the sense of Zionism and going to Israel was so well embedded into us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I'll give you an example.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Just two years ago, there was a 100-year anniversary with the first settlement of Bulgarian that settled in Hartuv.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So there was always that Zionist movement, that wanting to go back to Zion, wanting to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So that was a tremendous desire on our part, through our religious affiliation at home, through our affiliation outside of-- of home, through the school, the affiliation with the Maccabi organization.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we were always into Judaism and Jewishness and the customs and wanting always go back to-- to-- it was a dream for us always to go back to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the beginning, it was very sketchy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first thing was when-- like I said, when my father was restricted from traveling.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Second thing was, like I said to you, the most flagrant thing was when my father's boss came from Germany and he witnessed the persecution there and the Jews being hold to-- to our sidewalks.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and he saw all of that and he was able to come back and not be detained because he enjoyed the privilege of being a former Bulgarian officer.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So as a Jew, he still had certain privileges that he was able to come back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there were others that never came back, that they were on trips and they were-- they remained there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They just closed Germany and that was it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we begin to get a real bad feeling after that, because there was the Fascist movement in Bulgaria.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was the law in defense of the nation.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
